properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 24 at 2:43AM CST until January 24 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Light to Moderate Snow Continues Over Southeast Iowa This
Morning...

.Low pressure in Missouri has spread snow over eastern into south
central Iowa this morning with snow totals generally between 3 and
4 inches by sunrise this morning. Though little wind is
anticipated, roads will be impacted during the morning commute.

* WHAT...Snow and freezing drizzle. Additional snow accumulations
of 1 to 3 inches and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Southeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until noon CST today.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery and snow covered road conditions.
The hazardous conditions will impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY
